Each print spool generation phase produces at least one Processing Lot and one Spool Set.

A Processing Lot classifies the Shipments and groups them together depending on the actions to be performed on each one. For example, it is possible to create a number of Processing Lots, one for each sheets range, and assign the Shipments to them depending on the number of sheets they contain. A different Overprint configuration can be specified for each Processing Lot.

A Spool Set classifies the Shipments depending on the way in which they will actually be grouped together to deliver them to the print spool users. For example, a printing, mailing and shipping process might need to receive Spool Sets of a size that can be printed on a single roll of paper, to allow the plant to be re-set up between one set and the next.

Document Composition allows creation of one Spool Set for each Processing Lot, or allows all the Processing Lots to be delivered in the same Spool Set.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## **Lot Settings**
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

Processing Lot configuration allows you to set the number of groups the Shipments produced by Document Composition during print spool generation are to be separated into.

The most common Processing Lot configurations are illustrated below:

**Name**

**Description**

**Single lot**

All shipments are directed to the same Processing Lot.

**One lot per sheets range**

If Envelopes with different numbers of sheets have to be processed differently, a

Processing Lot is created for each sheets range, plus one for all the Envelopes that do

not belong to any known group.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Creating a processing lot
- In the **Output settings **exploration panel, click on **New**.

- Click **Lot...**.

- Enter a lot code in the **New lot **window.

> Note

If a serializer was selected when **Lot **was clicked, it will be displayed in the **Create lot** window in the** Serializer** menu; otherwise, the menu will be empty.

- Select the required Serializer.

- Click **New **or press **Enter **to confirm the creation and close the window.

> Warning

The Processing Lot creation window performs a validation on the code entered. If the code field is empty or is the same as another code already used in the Serializer, creation is not possible.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Changing the code of a processing lot
- From the **Output settings **exploration panel, click the name of the Processing Lot whose code you wish to modify.

- Click **Change... **next to the Lot code.

- Enter the new code in the **Modify lot **window

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- Click **Apply **or press **Enter **to confirm the modification and close the window.

> Warning

The Modify lot window performs a validation on the code entered. If the identifier field is empty or is the same as another code already used in the Serializer, the modification is not possible.

### Changing the name of a processing lot
- From the **Output settings **exploration panel, click the name of the Processing Lot whose name you wish to modify.

- Double click the name of the Processing Lot to access modification mode.

- Change the name and click **Enter **to confirm.

> Tip

If you have more than one Processing Lot, press [tab] to move from one Processing Lot to another without losing the modification mode.

### Deleting a processing lot
- Click the name of the lot you wish to delete in the **Output settings **exploration panel.

- Click **Delete lot...**.

- In the confirmation prompt window, click **Delete **to confirm the operation and close the window.
